# Convex Deployment Configuration

Current deployment guidance for this repo.

## Production

Pindeck uses the self-hosted Convex deployment on Hostinger:

| Surface | URL |
|---|---|
| Convex API and WebSocket | `https://convex.serving.cloud` |
| Convex HTTP actions | `https://convex-site.serving.cloud` |

The former `tremendous-jaguar-953.convex.cloud` / `.convex.site` deployment is
retired guidance and must not be used for Pindeck production work.

## Production-first local workflow

The ignored `.env.local` should contain:

```text
CONVEX_SELF_HOSTED_URL=https://convex.serving.cloud
VITE_CONVEX_URL=https://convex.serving.cloud
VITE_CONVEX_SITE_URL=https://convex-site.serving.cloud
```

Load `CONVEX_SELF_HOSTED_ADMIN_KEY` from BWS secret
`PROXMOX_HOME_HOSTINGER_CONVEX_CURRENT_ADMIN_KEY` or the gitignored
`proxmox-home/secrets/credentials.private.md`. Do not put its value in tracked
files, chat, or logs.

Run the frontend only:

```bash
bun run dev:frontend
```

Avoid `convex dev` while targeting production because it can overwrite local
environment defaults.

## Deploy backend changes

After editing `convex/*`, load the self-hosted URL/admin key and run:

```bash
bun run deploy:convex
```

`package.json` maps this to `convex deploy`.

## Trigger.dev split

Convex production runtime owns these server-only values:

- `TRIGGER_API_URL=https://trigger.v1su4.dev`
- `TRIGGER_SECRET_KEY` from BWS `PINDECK_TRIGGER_SECRET_KEY`
- `PINDECK_ORCHESTRATION_TOKEN` from BWS `PINDECK_ORCHESTRATION_TOKEN`
- `PINDECK_TRIGGER_ORCHESTRATION_ENABLED`

Trigger.dev production owns:

- `PINDECK_CONVEX_SITE_URL=https://convex-site.serving.cloud`
- `PINDECK_ORCHESTRATION_TOKEN` with the same value as Convex/BWS

The browser must never receive any Trigger secret, orchestration token, Convex
admin key, or provider key.

## Vercel build notes

- Frontend build command is `bun run build` (Vite build only).
- Do not run `convex dev --once` in the Vercel build.
- Convex, Trigger.dev, and Vercel deployments are separate operations.

## Other environment boundaries

Convex backend/runtime:

- `INGEST_API_KEY`
- `DISCORD_STATUS_WEBHOOK_URL`
- `OPEN_ROUTER_KEY` / `OPENROUTER_API_KEY`
- `FAL_KEY`

Frontend/Vercel:

- `VITE_CONVEX_URL`
- `VITE_CONVEX_SITE_URL`

Discord worker:

- `DISCORD_TOKEN`, `DISCORD_CLIENT_ID`, `DISCORD_GUILD_ID`
- `PINDECK_USER_ID`
- `INGEST_API_KEY`
- `CONVEX_SITE_URL` or explicit Pindeck ingest/moderation URLs

Vercel does not host the Discord websocket worker; it remains an always-on
separate service.
